title: Former Coach Backs Matildas For Asian Cup Glory | 10 News
description: He once coached the Matildas and now Ante Milicic says the team could prove hard to beat ahead of next month's Asian Cup on home soil. title: Teen Run Over Three Times, Attacked With Cleaver In Violent St Kilda Rampage | 10 News
description: Fed up police have likened the outrageous, violent behaviour of a group of thugs at St Kilda last night to a pack of rabid dogs.  The group hunted down a teenager in a rental car, running over him three times and attacking him with a meat cleaver.  Neighbours who witnessed the confrontation were left stunned and traumatised. title: Bondi Rescue's Gift To Boy, Teen Brothers Chasing ICE, WNBA Star Down Under | 10 News+
description: The Bondi Rescue crew have made an eight-year-old boy with cerebral palsy’s day by helping him experience the iconic beach for the first time after the child was kicked out of an inflatable pool on Australia Day.  The world of WNBA is growing at pace and it’s thanks to elite players like Angel Reese - but she reveals the one thing that always gets her in trouble.  Two young brothers are putting their teenage years on pause to follow ICE agents and their immigration enforcement across the US so they can document and share everything.  Should there be a national standard for tradies to stop work on extreme heat days?  It comes as the Queensland CFMEU is pushing for a mandatory, statewide "down tools" policy to protect construction workers from extreme heat when temperatures hit 35 degrees.
